BRYAN et al. v. HUNTINGTON. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. February 10, 1902.) No. 283. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of West Virginia, at Parkersburg. Z. T. Vinson and W. K. Cowden, for appellants. Maxwell Evarts and F. B. Enslow, for appellee.

Before SIMONTON, Circuit Judge, and MORRIS and BOYD, District Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Considering the assignments of error in this case and the arguments of counsel thereon, it is ordered the appeal be dismissed, and the decree of the circuit court affirmed. The reasons for this action will be filed hereafter.
